# Typography Component - Quick Reference

## Rule: ALWAYS use Typography component for ALL text

**NEVER use inline text styling with Tailwind classes!**

## Quick Usage

```tsx
import Typography from 'components/ui/typography/typography.component';

<Typography 
  type="h3" 
  size="body16" 
  weight="semibold" 
  color="black"
  className="mb-1"
>
  Your Text
</Typography>
```

## Common Patterns

```tsx
// Section titles
<Typography type="h2" size="body16" weight="bold" color="gray">
  Section Title
</Typography>

// Item titles  
<Typography type="h3" size="body16" weight="semibold" color="black">
  Item Title
</Typography>

// Body text / descriptions
<Typography type="p" size="body14" color="gray">
  Description text
</Typography>

// Button text (when using Typography)
<Typography type="span" size="default" weight="bold" color="black">
  Button Text
</Typography>
```

## Size Naming Convention

- Use `body[size]` format: `body14`, `body16`, `body18`, `body20`, etc.
- Always based on pixel values from Figma
- Desktop: defined in `size` property
- Mobile: defined in `mobileSize` property

## Before Creating Component

1. ✅ Extract typography specs from Figma design
2. ✅ Check if sizes/weights/colors exist in `typography.variants.data.tsx`
3. ✅ Add missing variants following `body[size]` naming
4. ✅ Never use Tailwind text-*, font-*, leading-* classes directly

## Adding New Typography Variants

When Figma specifies typography not in the project:

```tsx
// 1. Add to typography.variants.data.tsx
size: {
  body16: "md:text-[16px] md:leading-[24px]",  // Desktop
},
mobileSize: {
  body16: "text-[16px] leading-[24px]",        // Mobile
},
color: {
  black: "text-[#000017]",  // From Figma color specs
  gray: "text-[#666674]",
},
weight: {
  semibold: "font-semibold",  // weight: 600
},
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

```tsx
// ❌ Don't do this
<h3 className="text-lg font-bold text-black">Title</h3>
<span className="text-sm text-gray-600">Text</span>
<Typography size="body16" className="text-lg font-bold">  // Conflicting styles

// ✅ Do this instead
<Typography type="h3" size="body16" weight="bold" color="black">Title</Typography>
<Typography type="span" size="body14" color="gray">Text</Typography>
<Typography type="h3" size="body16" weight="bold" color="black" className="mb-2">
```

## Props Reference

- **type**: Semantic HTML element (`h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `p`, `span`, etc.)
- **size**: Typography size variant (`body14`, `body16`, etc.)
- **weight**: Font weight (`default`, `semibold`, `bold`, etc.)
- **color**: Text color (`black`, `gray`, `white`, etc.)
- **className**: Additional Tailwind classes (spacing, alignment only - NO typography styles!)

